SIMPLE: deerstalker
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deerstalker
<hw>Deer"stalk`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who practices deerstalking.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A close-fitting cap, usually woolen, such as is worn
in deerstalking, having a low crown and visors both in front and back,
and having earflaps which are usually worn tied together over the top;
also called <altname>fore-and-after</altname>, <altname>deerstalker
hat</altname> and <altname>deerstalker cap</altname>; a hunter's cap;
formerly also used for any stiff, round hat.</def>
<mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deerstalking</ent>⟦br⟧
